A target date of mid-September has beenset for the signing of a package rescheduling Nigeria's mediumterm public sector debt and outstanding letter of creditclaims, Nigeria and Barclays Bank Plc said in a jointstatement.    The statement was issued during the last of a two daymeeting here between the two sides. Barclays is a co-chairmanof the commercial bank steering committee.    The statement said, "Further progress has been made in the1986/87 rescheduling of medium term public sector debt andoutstanding letter of credit claims." REUTER&#3;